    assessmentFindings: ["New-onset confusion, delirium, or cognitive decline suggesting anticholinergic toxicity or sedative accumulation","Falls or near-falls associated with orthostatic hypotension, over-sedation, or hypoglycemia","Unexplained GI symptoms (nausea, constipation, GI bleeding) from NSAIDs, opioids, or iron supplements","Electrolyte abnormalities: hypokalemia (diuretics), hyperkalemia (ACE inhibitors/ARBs), hyponatremia (SSRIs/thiazides)","Signs of bleeding (bruising, petechiae, melena, hematuria) from anticoagulant-antiplatelet-NSAID interactions","Renal function decline requiring medication dose adjustments","QTc prolongation risk from multiple QT-prolonging medications (fluoroquinolones, antipsychotics, ondansetron)"],
