    pearls: ["The Drug Burden Index (DBI) quantifies cumulative anticholinergic and sedative exposure -- higher DBI scores correlate with increased falls, cognitive impairment, and functional decline in older adults","Serum creatinine alone is unreliable in elderly patients due to decreased muscle mass -- always use eGFR or Cockcroft-Gault creatinine clearance for medication dosing decisions","Prescribing cascades are a hallmark of polypharmacy harm: antihypertensive causes ankle edema, diuretic prescribed for edema causes hypokalemia, potassium supplement causes GI upset, antiemetic prescribed -- recognize and interrupt the cascade","The STOPP/START criteria are more sensitive than Beers Criteria for detecting prescribing omissions (beneficial medications not prescribed) in addition to potentially inappropriate medications","QTc prolongation risk increases multiplicatively with each QT-prolonging medication added -- always check baseline ECG when prescribing combinations of fluoroquinolones, antipsychotics, SSRIs, or ondansetron","Never abruptly discontinue beta-blockers (rebound hypertension/angina), corticosteroids (adrenal crisis), benzodiazepines (seizures), or SSRIs (discontinuation syndrome) -- taper all CNS-active and cardiovascular medications systematically"],
